
[Richmond, 19 Mch. 1781. Minute in War Office Journal (Vi) under this date: A letter from the Governor respecting ammunition &c. required by Cap: Mitch [Mitchell]. Waited on the Governor in consequence of it. And sent off the following letters containing orders for the ammunition, &c. immediately. A letter to Cap. Browne, State Commissary [184] of Military Stores. To Cap. Irish. To Mr. Moody, and to the Commanding officer of the State Garrison Regiment. And an order to the Quarter Master to furnish a Waggon to carry the ammunition, &c. to Turkey Island. TJs letter has not been located. Copies of Muters letters to the persons mentioned above are in War Office Letter Book (Vi).]
